{
  "issue": {
    "expand": "renderedFields,names,schema,operations,editmeta,changelog,versionedRepresentations,customfield_10010.requestTypePractice",
    "id": "11631",
    "self": "https://shulman-hill.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/issue/11631",
    "key": "SH-115",
    "fields": {
      "summary": "Referral Zapier Failures",
      "attachment": [],
      "created": "2025-11-11T14:30:37.536-0700",
      "duedate": null,
      "description": {
        "type": "doc",
        "version": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The \"Firm to M&M - Continuous Updates\" Zap in Zapier is experiencing exponential growth in daily execution volume. Zap runs increased up to 1,300/day, consuming the Zapier task allocation."
              },
              {
                "type": "hardBreak"
              },
              {
                "type": "hardBreak"
              },
              {
                "type": "hardBreak"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The scheduled flow `M_M_Portal_Update_Daily_Scheduled_Flow` identifies referral records that need portal updates but relies on the `Referral_After_Save` flow to set `Next_M_M_Portal_Update__c` to a future date. When the after-save flow fails (likely duplicate detection errors) or when `M_M_Portal_Updated_Trigger__c` doesn't change from false to true, `Next_M_M_Portal_Update__c` remains null or in the past, causing records to be reprocessed daily."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      "customfield_10010": null,
      "reporter": {
